----- cvs ci ------
Sun Oct 24 16:58:04 NOVST 1999
max (patch from Kolya Nesterov):
- carbonCopy & carbonMove implemented in hpt
- carbons in netmail are possible (used to implement mailboxes)
  to use this define transit netmail area (it must be first in
  config), and your private netmail area(s)
  Then add something like this to fidoconfig:
    CarbonTo Kolya Nesterov
    CarbonMove kolya.netmail
- carbonExtern: spawns external program with the last parameter equal
  to temp file with msg header & text or pipes it to the external program
  if first char of command line is '|' (to use this pipe feature you must
  have popen function in your system and define HAS_POPEN symbol in makefile
  (already done for linux))
- pktinfo: added switches -h (display header msg info) and -t (display msg
  text) (could be used instead of various pkt viewers)
- packBadArea - checks for link write access to area added
- some internal changes in scan.c: decreased the number of functions,
  all argument for scan are also possible to pack

